Hantavirus pulmonary syndrome - Chile (Santiago) 20001107.1948
Date: 8 Nov 2000 14:02:03 -0400
From: : Pablo Vial <pvial@med.puc.cl>

Clarification of diagnosis
--------------------------
The case reported here developed a mild form of the disease caused by
hantavirus infection [infection by one of the hantaviruses , and did not
developed hanta cardiopulmonary syndrome. Individuals with documented
recent infection by Hantavirus with benign clinical course (mild symptoms
or completely asymptomatic) have been reported before, in the US, Argentina
and Chile. The woman with this mild clinical course of Hantavirus infection
reported by the Chilean authorities, has laboratory confirmation;
anti-hantavirus IgM antibodies were detected by ELISA (technique and
capture antigen developed by CDC), strip blot for hantavirus antibodies was
also positive (technique and capture antigen developed by University of New
Mexico researchers). Hantavirus RT-PCR from a plasma sample and PMBCs were
also positive.
--
Pablo A. Vial
Virology Lab
Universidad Catolica de Chile
<pvial@med.puc.cl>
